title: Corn Bulls Spread Holiday Cheer on Wednesday
all_text:
Corn futures rounded out the pre-Christmas session with contracts 3 to 4 cents higher. The CmdtyView national average Cash Corn price was up 3 1/2 cent to $4.07 1/2. The markets will be closed for Christmas on Thursday with a hard open at 8:30 am CST on Friday.
Export Sales data has total corn export commitments at 47.579 MMT as of December 11, which is 31% above a year ago. That is also 59% of USDA’s record projection, in line with the 57% average sales pace. Actual shipments are 28% of that projection, ahead of the 19% 5-year average.
The Buenos Aires Grain Exchange estimates the Argentina corn crop at 77.7% planted, ahead of average, with conditions of the crop emerged rated at 87% good/excellent, compared to 38% last year.

title: Corn Bulls Looking to Head into Christmas Break with Strength
all_text:
Corn prices are up 1 to 2 cents so far on Wednesday. Futures closed Tuesday with contracts fractionally to a penny higher. Preliminary open interest was up 946 contracts on Tuesday. The CmdtyView national average Cash Corn price was up 1/2 cent to $4.03. The markets will close early on Wednesday and remain closed for Christmas on Thursday with a hard open at 8:30 am CST on Friday.
The Tuesday USDA Export Sales update for the week of 12/11 showed 1.74 MMT of corn. That was a 17.9% increase from the data released on Monday for the week prior and 48.5% above the same week last year. Export sale commitments, which are now nearly caught up from the government shutdown, are 31% above the same week last year at 47.58 MMT (1.873 bbu).
CFTC’s Commitment of Traders report for the week ending last Tuesday December 16 showed spec traders in corn futures and options flipping back to a net long position of 52,672 contracts. That was a move to 62,390 contracts to the short side during that week with a mix of new shorts and fewer longs.
EIA data, normally out on Wednesday, will be delayed until Monday due to the government taking the December 24-26 off.

title: Soybean Bulls Open Christmas Presents Early on Wednesday
all_text:
Soybean futures were in a jolly mood leading into the Christmas break, with contracts 11 to 14 cents higher. The cmdtyView national average Cash Bean price was 11 3/4 cents higher at $9.92 3/4. Soymeal futures posted gains of $3 to $3.80 on Wednesday, as Soy Oil futures were up 65 to 74 points. The markets will be closed for Christmas on Thursday with a hard open at 8:30 am CST on Friday.
USDA has export sale commitments for soybeans at 25.778 MMT, which is down 33% from the same period last year as of 12/11. That it 58% of USDA’s export projection and lagging the 79% average pace.
Buenos Aires Grains Exchange data showed 75.5% of the soybean crop planted, below the average pace. Condition ratings were pegged at 67% good/excellent, which is 5 points above last year.

title: Wheat Prices Are Headed for Their Longest Rally Since April. How You Should Play Futures Here.
all_text:
March HRW wheat (KEH26) futures present a buying opportunity on more price strength.
See on the daily bar chart for March hard red winter wheat futures that prices Tuesday hit a three-week high. See, too, at the bottom of the chart that the moving average convergence divergence indicator has just produced a buy signal as the blue MACD line has crossed above the red trigger line.
Fundamentally, wheat futures are headed for a fifth straight up day today, the longest rally since April, as Black Sea supply risks and weather uncertainties support prices. Russian forces launched a missile and drone attack across Ukraine on Tuesday, killing civilians and damaging energy and port facilities in the Odesa region on the Black Sea, according to Ukrainian officials. Dryness is also building in U.S. HRW wheat-growing regions, adding to support for prices. “Dry weather accompanies record-setting warmth across the central and southern Plains,” the USDA said in a Tuesday report.
A move in March HRW wheat futures above chart resistance at $5.35 would give the bulls more power and it would also become a buying opportunity. The upside price objective would be $6.20 or above. Technical support, for which to place a protective sell stop just below, is located at $5.00.

title: Wheat prices rise, heads for longest rally since April amid supply uncertainties
all_text:
In the US growing regions, dryness is also increasing, supporting prices. According to a study from forecaster Vaisala, the circumstances are predicted to persist this week, sustaining moisture shortages in both northern and southern regions.
By CNBCTV18.com
Chicago wheat futures increased for a fifth session, setting up the longest advance since April. This is happening due to concerns about Black Sea supplies and the inclement weather.
According to Ukraine, Russian soldiers attacked Ukraine with missiles and drones on Tuesday, killing civilians and destroying port and energy infrastructure in the Black Sea town of Odesa. This contributes to a recent wave of attacks that have harmed both nations' infrastructure.
The two nations are significant exporters of edible oils and grains, and the escalating hostilities pose a threat to regional supplies.
